<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7350&amp;p=72387#p72387"><![CDATA[
And if he's loading a file marked with the "CHR" type it's reasonable to assume that it's never compressed, as it's supposed to be loaded directly to CHR-RAM by the BIOS. Though it may be possible that some of the hackish programmers treat CHR-RAM as some generic space for storage I think it's rare (if not non-existent) considering how useful this could be.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4653">Gilbert</a> — Thu Jan 06, 2011 6:15 am</p><hr />
